                    angular -front end development

             Basic command

        1.to create project - ng new project-name/ng new project-name --routing

        2.to run a project - ng serve /ng serve --opem

        3.to create component - ng g c component -name

        4.// open folder in src service and then  to create servics - ng g s service -name 


                Basuic Concepts

        1.Component -to create {html,css,file} root component -App component

        2.Module - to add libraries to the project root module - AppModule

        3.Data Binding - data sharing between html and ts

             3.1 One way Binding
                
               3.1.1 component(ts) to view(html)

                 3.1.1.1  string Interpolation :syntax -{{variable-name}}

                 3.1.1.2  Property Binding : syntax - [attribute]="variable-name"

              3.1.2 view(html) to component(ts)

                 3.1.2.1  Event Binding -(event)="function-call()"

                 3.1.2.2 Event Binding using $event-(event)="function-call($event)"

                 3.1.2.3 Template referencing variable-synatx:#variable-name 

            3.2 Two way Binding

              3.2.1 using ngModel -Import FormsModule in AppModule,synatx-{(ngModel)}="variable-name"   


        4.To setup path for a component : defined in App Routing Module
                syntax:{path:'',componenet:componenetClassName} 

        5. Dependency Injection - to share data between classes        

        6.Angular servics - for reduntant data or to reuse data

        7.ngSubmit - to submit entire form syntax: (ngSubmit)="function-call"

        8.Angular Forms

                8.1 Template driven Forms-irst design html

                8.2 Model Driven Forms - first create model in ts

                        8.2.1 Reactive Forms-Add validation: Import ReactiveformsModule
                                -Form group-FormBuilder(eggGroup)-inject dependency ,Form array,Form control


        9.Angular Directives - To manipulate DOM(Document Object Model)

                9.1 Component Directives

                9.2 Structural directives - To change DOM structure 

                   9.2.1   ngIf - syntax:*ngIf="condition"


        10. local storage - to permanently store data in browser

                10.1 setItem()           

                10.2 getItem()

                10.3 removeItem()

                






